comments.body: The very few B. oligolepis we have seen have a greenish overall coloration... but theres probably some color variation among specimens.. It could also be juvenile coloration
@wolfgang_wuster  youve probably noticed it is quite far out of B. oligolepis known distribution range

identifications.body:
That's not *Bothrops atrox*. Scale shape, eye colour, head shape and narrow postocular band are all wrong, as is the interrupted light line along the lower flanks. I would suspect something from the phylogenetic neighbourhood of *B. oligolepis*, but it does not really match any description of any of those species that I am familiar with.

@mossambica ?

non_owner_ids.body:
That's not *Bothrops atrox*. Scale shape, eye colour, head shape and narrow postocular band are all wrong, as is the interrupted light line along the lower flanks. I would suspect something from the phylogenetic neighbourhood of *B. oligolepis*, but it does not really match any description of any of those species that I am familiar with.

@mossambica ?
